---
import LegalLayout from "../layouts/LegalLayout.astro";
import { site } from "../config/site";

const lastUpdated = "May 24, 2026";
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${site.name} collects, uses, and protects your information.`}
  lastUpdated={lastUpdated}
>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy describes how <strong>{site.name}</strong> (&ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or
    &ldquo;our&rdquo;) handles information when you use our website, sign in with Google or other providers,
    run desktop or mobile clients, or connect optional integrations such as Spotify or Google Classroom.
  </p>
  <p>
    By using JARVIS, you agree to this policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the service.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Who we are</h2>
  <p>
    JARVIS is a personal AI execution system: natural language is converted into structured intent and
    executed on devices you control. Contact: <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
  <h3>Account and authentication</h3>
  <p>When you sign in (for example with Google OAuth), we may receive:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>A stable provider subject identifier and basic profile fields (such as name and email) as permitted by the provider.</li>
    <li>OAuth tokens required to maintain your session and, with your consent, to access connected services.</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Voice and conversation</h3>
  <p>
    If you use voice features, audio may be processed for speech-to-text on your device or via configured
    backend services. Conversation text and generated responses may be stored to provide continuity and
    improve your experience when memory features are enabled.
  </p>
  <h3>Execution and device data</h3>
  <p>
    Commands, task status, device identifiers used for pairing, and logs needed to operate the executor may
    be processed. Many actions run locally on your machine; only data required for remote control or cloud
    sync is transmitted to our servers.
  </p>
  <h3>Preferences and optional imports</h3>
  <p>
    Onboarding preferences, personality sliders, and optional imported JSON or taste data (e.g. Spotify likes,
    YouTube history) are stored per account when you provide them. You can skip optional steps.
  </p>
  <h3>Website</h3>
  <p>
    Our public site may log standard technical data (IP address, browser type, pages viewed) for security and
    operations. We do not use invasive third-party advertising trackers on this site.
  </p>

  <h2>3. How we use information</h2>
  <p>We use collected information to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Authenticate you and manage your account and sessions.</li>
    <li>Parse requests, plan tasks, and execute commands you initiate.</li>
    <li>Personalize behavior according to your stated preferences.</li>
    <li>Operate, secure, and improve JARVIS; diagnose errors; comply with law.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information.</p>

  <h2>4. Legal bases (where applicable)</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your region, we rely on performance of a contract (providing the service), legitimate
    interests (security, improvement), and consent (optional integrations and certain processing).
  </p>

  <h2>5. Sharing and subprocessors</h2>
  <p>We may share data with:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Identity providers</strong> (e.g. Google) when you choose to sign in or connect an integration.</li>
    <li><strong>Infrastructure and AI providers</strong> you or we configure (e.g. hosting, model APIs) solely to deliver features you use.</li>
    <li><strong>Legal authorities</strong> when required by law or to protect rights and safety.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Third-party services have their own privacy policies. OAuth tokens for integrations like Google Classroom
    or Spotify are stored according to product settings and can be revoked by disconnecting the integration
    or deleting your account.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain account and preference data while your account is active. Logs and conversation history may be
    retained for a limited period for operations and, where enabled, memory features. You may request deletion
    as described below.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use reasonable technical and organizational measures (encryption in transit, access controls, secure
    token storage patterns). No method of transmission or storage is 100% secure; use strong device security
    and protect your account credentials.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Your rights and choices</h2>
  <p>Depending on your location, you may have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Access, correct, or export your personal data.</li>
    <li>Delete your account and associated preferences and memory data.</li>
    <li>Withdraw consent for optional processing.</li>
    <li>Object to or restrict certain processing.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    To exercise these rights, contact <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>. You may
    also revoke OAuth access in your Google Account settings at
    <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"
      >myaccount.google.com/permissions</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Children</h2>
  <p>
    JARVIS is not directed at children under 13 (or the minimum age in your jurisdiction). We do not knowingly
    collect data from children.
  </p>

  <h2>10. International transfers</h2>
  <p>
    If you use JARVIS from outside the country where our servers run, your data may be processed in other
    regions with appropriate safeguards where required.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this policy. We will post the new date at the top of this page. Material changes may be
    communicated through the app or email where appropriate.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions about this Privacy Policy: <a href={`mailto:${site.contactEmail}`}>{site.contactEmail}</a>.
    See also our <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
